statement.p:
If r is a relation on a set A and \lvert A \rvert = n, then the transitive closure of r is the union of the first n powers of
r.  That is, 
r^+ = r \cup  r^2 \cup  r ^3 \cup \cdots  \cup  r^n\text{.}

program.input:
1.0 T = R
2.0 for k = 1 to n:
     for i = 1 to n:
      for j = 1 to n:
        T[i,j]= T[i,j] + T[i,k] * T[k,j]
3.0 Return T
